  "prompt": "What are some greatest operations by Ajit Doval?",
  "response": "Ajit Doval, the National Security Advisor of India, has been involved in various significant operations throughout his career in intelligence and security. Some of the most notable operations attributed to him include:\n\n1. **Mizoram Insurgency**: Doval is credited with having infiltrated the Mizo National Front to negotiate an end to insurgent activities. His efforts reportedly led to the signing of the Mizoram Accord in 1986.\n\n2. **Operation Black Thunder**: Doval was instrumental in the success of Operation Black Thunder, which aimed to flush out militants from the Golden Temple in Amritsar in 1988. He disguised himself as a rickshaw puller to gain inside information.\n\n3. **Kandahar Hijacking**: During the 1999 Indian Airlines IC-814 hijacking, Doval was one of the key negotiators who worked to secure the release of hostages.\n\n4. **Anti-Terrorism Operations**: Doval has played a crucial role in strategizing and overseeing various anti-terrorism operations across India, including the neutralization of terror cells and operatives.\n\n5. **Surgical Strikes**: Doval was pivotal in the planning and execution of the 2016 surgical strikes conducted by India across the Line of Control in Pakistan-occupied Kashmir, targeting terrorist launch pads.\n\n6. **2019 Balakot Airstrike**: He played a significant strategic role in the planning of the Balakot airstrike, where Indian Air Force jets targeted a terrorist training camp inside Pakistan.\n\nAjit Doval's career has been marked by his deep involvement in ensuring India's national security through intelligence, covert operations, and direct action against threats. His work has made a significant impact on India's security landscape.",
